{
  "texts": [
    "In addition to the above work, several efforts have been made to develop contract theory models under prospect theory to facilitate user-centric sensing data sharing [16].",
    "Despite these advancements, the application of diffusionbased contract theory for data sharing remains unexplored.",
    "While existing contract theory models are valuable, they often fall short of addressing the intricate challenges associated with the dynamic and multifaceted nature of data sharing.",
    "In many real-world contexts, data sharing is not a simple transaction but a process spanning multiple stages and involving diverse participants [28].",
    "Diffusion-based contract theory incorporates the spread and evolution of information over time and space, enabling a deeper understanding of incentives and behaviors among data holders and users [17]."
  ]
}